    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "After bailing out Silicon Valley Bank last week, the federal government is "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "reportedly considering"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " the rescue of a second struggling institution whose "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            1
          ],
          1,
          "deposits are largely uninsured"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ". But just two months ago, that bank, San Francisco-based First Republic, pressured regulators not to adopt new rules to minimize the risk of government bailouts for insolvent banks, calling such enhanced regulation ‚Äúunnecessary.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic Bank is best-known for its "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          1,
          "role"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " at the center of a major Donald Trump scandal. Its board of directors includes "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            3
          ],
          1,
          "major Trump donor"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " and "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            4
          ],
          1,
          "ally"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " Tom Barrack, who is "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            5
          ],
          1,
          "reportedly"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " spearheading efforts to save the company."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Only months before the rescue talk began, the bank waged a battle to deter federal banking regulators from considering stronger measures to prepare for the potential failures of regional banks like First Republic."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Under laws passed after the 2008 financial crisis, large banks are already required to show that, if they fail, the process of shutting them down will not imperil the broader financial system or rely on taxpayer money."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      1
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "A 2018 regulatory rollback "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            6
          ],
          1,
          "reduced many requirements"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " on regional banks, including that they draw up annual plans, known as ‚Äúliving wills,‚Äù to safely wind down failing banks. But as those banks "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            7
          ],
          1,
          "rapidly ballooned in size"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", federal regulators "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            8
          ],
          1,
          "solicited public comment last fall"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " on whether additional precautions were needed to limit the risk of financial contagion in the event of ‚Äúuninsured depositors suffering loss‚Äù at one bank."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "That is the very prospect now facing customers of First Republic, about "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            1
          ],
          1,
          "two-thirds of whose deposits are uninsured"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " because they surpass the $250,000 guaranteed by the federal government."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      2
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The proposal drew predictable opposition from bank lobbying groups, but First Republic CEO Michael Roffler also "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            9
          ],
          1,
          "weighed in personally"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", saying the measures were ‚Äúunnecessary‚Äù for banks without complex corporate structures, including First Republic. Existing regulations, which require the bank to submit a so-called resolution plan for its insolvency every three years, were sufficient, he argued."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúIn the unlikely event of insolvency of the bank, the resolution process should be straightforward,‚Äù "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            9
          ],
          1,
          "wrote Roffler in January"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", arguing that his bank should not be required to hold additional capital or issue additional ‚Äú"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            10
          ],
          1,
          "loss-absorbing‚Äù unsecured long-term debt"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", one of the measures under consideration by regulators to add to banks‚Äô financial cushion in times of crisis."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Now, less than two months later, First Republic is on the brink of insolvency and "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            11
          ],
          1,
          "struggling to "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "raise emergency capital following some "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            12
          ],
          1,
          "$70 billion in depositor withdrawals"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " in recent weeks."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The bank staved off collapse this month with an "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            13
          ],
          1,
          "unprecedented $30 billion emergency infusion from other banks"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", but still faces a hole in its books. Industry leaders and federal officials are now discussing the possibility of government backing for a rescue deal, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          0,
          "according to "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          2,
          "Bloomberg News"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic Bank declined "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          1,
          "The Lever"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚Äôs request for comment. A spokesperson for the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC), one of the two agencies considering the enhanced resolution requirements, said it does not discuss open and operating institutions. A spokesperson for the other agency, the Federal Reserve, declined to comment."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h3",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúTrigger-Prone‚Äù Depositors"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic Bank‚Äôs financial woes are similar, though not identical, to those of Silicon Valley Bank (SVB)."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Both institutions held long-term assets hit hard by the Federal Reserve‚Äôs recent interest rate hikes, and both had large numbers of uninsured depositors ‚Äî two key risk factors that put nearly 190 other banks at risk of the same fate as SVB, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            15
          ],
          1,
          "according to a recent academic study"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic and SVB also share a Silicon Valley pedigree. While SVB was the go-to banker and lender for start-up businesses, First Republic found its niche among well-heeled individuals in tech, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            16
          ],
          1,
          "operating a branch"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " inside Facebook‚Äôs Menlo Park headquarters and "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            17
          ],
          1,
          "giving CEO Mark Zuckerberg"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " a $6 million mortgage-loan at an interest rate of 1.05 percent."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      3
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "While First Republic built a loyal following among some of its clientele ‚Äî the founder of a male fertility-focused start-up called AlphaSperm told the "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            18,
            14
          ],
          2,
          "San Francisco Chronicle"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          1,
          " "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "that he planned to weather the storm ‚Äî its elite customer base also posed a special risk."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúThese depositors are particularly trigger-prone,‚Äù Boston College law professor "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            19
          ],
          1,
          "Patricia McCoy told CNN"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " of the bank run on First Republic that began in the wake of SVB‚Äôs collapse, which was itself precipitated by a "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            20
          ],
          1,
          "rapid exodus"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " of venture capitalists like Peter Thiel. ‚ÄúThey‚Äôre sophisticated, they know they have other options, and they have mechanisms in place to move money quickly.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "SVB both lent heavily to and "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            21
          ],
          1,
          "invested directly in"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " venture capital funds. While these activities made up less of First Republic‚Äôs business, the bank has $10 billion of such loans on its books."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic is using nearly all of its deposits to fund its lending activities, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            22
          ],
          1,
          "according to Morningstar"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", increasing the risk that it could run out of cash to cover withdrawals."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "First Republic and SVB share another key commonality: They both had assets sitting just below the $250 billion threshold at which banks "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            23
          ],
          1,
          "are subject to"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " annual stress tests and other enhanced regulations."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The 2010 Dodd-Frank financial reform law set that threshold at $50 billion, but a 2018 bipartisan deregulatory law raised it. SVB CEO Greg Becker personally pressed Congress to reduce scrutiny of regional banks like his own, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            24
          ],
          0,
          "as "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          1,
          "The Lever "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          1,
          "reported earlier this month."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h3",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúBefore They Fail‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "In the wake of the 2018 law and the subsequent relaxation of oversight by the Federal Reserve, both "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            25
          ],
          1,
          "First Republic"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " and SVB grew rapidly, part of a "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            26
          ],
          1,
          "new wave of consolidation"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " in the banking sector."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "With advocates "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            27
          ],
          1,
          "raising the alarm"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " that mergers and rapid growth among regional banks now posed risks to the financial system, banking regulators in Joe Biden‚Äôs administration suggested last year that they would "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            7
          ],
          1,
          "consider increasing oversight"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "In October, the Federal Reserve and the FDIC issued a rulemaking notice "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            8
          ],
          1,
          "seeking public input"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " on whether some of the stringent requirements used to shield the financial system from the failure of so-called ‚Äúglobal systemically important banks‚Äù should also be applied to so-called midsize banks that have, in fact, grown quite large."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Stronger safeguards may be especially important, the agencies noted, given that ‚Äúsome large banking organizations have increased their reliance on large uninsured deposits to fund their operations over the past decade.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "While the largest banks also had high levels of uninsured deposits, existing regulations require them to submit annual living wills, and to maintain a larger financial cushion."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Financial reform groups said they support improved precautionary measures. But they took issue with the specific measure being contemplated by the Federal Reserve and the FDIC: requiring large banks "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            10
          ],
          1,
          "to issue forms of long-term debt"
